        public CommitQueueResult.Status getStatus()
        Return the status of the commit queue item.

        The status could be any of the following:

        #Status.NONE means that no device was involved in the transaction.

        #Status.ASYNC means that the transaction has successfully placed the configuration change for the participating devices in the commit queue.

        #Status.COMPLETED means that the queue item was successfully completed.

        #Status.TIMEOUT means that the timer expired before the queue item was completed.

        #Status.DELETED means that queue item was deleted from the queue.

        #Status.FAILED means that the queue item failed. The getFailedDevices() method will provide the error reason for each failed device.
